One person died and five others were seriously injured on Thursday when a matatu collided with a lorry in Gatunduri Village in Embu County.
Survivors suffered leg and hand fractures and were taken to the Embu Referral Hospital.
The lorry was heading to Embu from Meru when the collision occurred. The matatu was from the opposite direction. One passenger died on the spot.



