According to witnesses, the lorry was overtaking another vehicle when the collision occurred.
The accident caused a major traffic jam along the busy Embu-Meru highway as residents and police blocked the road to rescue passengers from the mangled matatu.
"I saw the lorry overtaking another vehicle before it ploughed into the matatu," a witness, Mr Patrick Mureithi, said.
Immediately after the accident, the lorry driver fled, leaving the matatu survivors groaning in pain.





Embu West police boss Charles Kinyua said the driver of the lorry was responsible for the accident and he was being sought.
"We are looking for the driver so that he can be prosecuted," he said.
Mr Kinyua said the driver will be charged with causing death by careless driving.
"The lorry driver knew he was in the wrong and that is why he fled but we are tracking him down," he said. Nakuru county government says bodies are congesting mortuaries. Though people lost jobs, they were able to grow their talents and became more creative. In his new year’s message to the country, the President called for a renewal of minds in the New Year 2021. He paraded the newly elected Msambweni MP Feisal Bader as the “firstborn” of the so called Hustler's Movement. Ever since Abiy Ahmed came to power, the Tigray regional government has been at odds with the central government.